{
  "video_id": "pHLP5CZMnL4",
  "title": "The microbial jungles all over the place (and you) - Scott Chimileski and Roberto Kolter",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 6949.0,
      "end_time": 9244.0,
      "text": "As we walk through our daily environments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 9244.0,
      "end_time": 11478.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re surrounded by exotic creatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 11478.0,
      "end_time": 14431.0,
      "text": "that are too small to see  with the naked eye."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 14431.0,
      "end_time": 18237.0,
      "text": "We usually imagine these  microscopic organisms, or microbes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 18237.0,
      "end_time": 22329.0,
      "text": "as asocial cells that float around by themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22329.0,
      "end_time": 25470.0,
      "text": "But in reality,  microbes gather by the millions"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 25470.0,
      "end_time": 30114.0,
      "text": "to form vast communities  known as biofilms."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 30114.0,
      "end_time": 33109.0,
      "text": "Natural biofilms are like  miniature jungles"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 33109.0,
      "end_time": 37582.0,
      "text": "filled with many kinds of microbes from across the web of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37582.0,
      "end_time": 40702.0,
      "text": "Bacteria and archaea mingle with other microbes"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 40702.0,
      "end_time": 43438.0,
      "text": "like algae, fungi, and protozoa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43438.0,
      "end_time": 48915.0,
      "text": "forming dense, organized structures that grow on almost any surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 48915.0,
      "end_time": 50677.0,
      "text": "When you pad across a river bottom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 50677.0,
      "end_time": 52939.0,
      "text": "touch the rind of an aged cheese,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52939.0,
      "end_time": 54483.0,
      "text": "tend your garden soil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 54483.0,
      "end_time": 56255.0,
      "text": "or brush your teeth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56255.0,
      "end_time": 60561.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re coming into contact with these invisible ecosystems."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 60561.0,
      "end_time": 63043.0,
      "text": "To see how biofilms come about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63043.0,
      "end_time": 67190.0,
      "text": "let&#39;s watch one as it develops on a submerged river rock."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 67190.0,
      "end_time": 70799.0,
      "text": "This type of biofilm might begin with a few bacteria"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 70799.0,
      "end_time": 73147.0,
      "text": "swimming through their liquid environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 73147.0,
      "end_time": 78076.0,
      "text": "The cells use rotating flagella to propel towards the surface of the rock,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 78076.0,
      "end_time": 82165.0,
      "text": "which they attach to with the help of sticky appendages."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 82165.0,
      "end_time": 85703.0,
      "text": "Then, they start producing an extracellular matrix"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 85703.0,
      "end_time": 89474.0,
      "text": "that holds them together as they divide and reproduce."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 89474.0,
      "end_time": 92495.0,
      "text": "Before long, microcolonies arise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 92495.0,
      "end_time": 96939.0,
      "text": "clusters of cells sheathed in this slimy, glue-like material."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96939.0,
      "end_time": 100055.0,
      "text": "Microcolonies grow to become towers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 100055.0,
      "end_time": 102632.0,
      "text": "while water channels flow around them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 102632.0,
      "end_time": 105207.0,
      "text": "functioning like a basic  circulatory system."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 105207.0,
      "end_time": 109143.0,
      "text": "But why do microbes build  such complex communities"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 109143.0,
      "end_time": 111129.0,
      "text": "when they could live alone?"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 111129.0,
      "end_time": 113739.0,
      "text": "For one thing, microbes  living in a biofilm"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 113739.0,
      "end_time": 117026.0,
      "text": "are rooted in a relatively  stable microenvironment"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117026.0,
      "end_time": 119793.0,
      "text": "where they may have access  to a nutrient source."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 119793.0,
      "end_time": 122303.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s also safety in numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 122303.0,
      "end_time": 125745.0,
      "text": "Out in the deep, dark wilderness of the microbial world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 125745.0,
      "end_time": 128644.0,
      "text": "isolated microbes face serious risks."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 128644.0,
      "end_time": 130191.0,
      "text": "Predators want to eat them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 130191.0,
      "end_time": 132509.0,
      "text": "immune systems seek to destroy them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 132509.0,
      "end_time": 134697.0,
      "text": "and there are physical dangers, too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 134697.0,
      "end_time": 137110.0,
      "text": "like running out of water and drying up."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 137110.0,
      "end_time": 140682.0,
      "text": "However, in a biofilm,  the extracellular matrix"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 140682.0,
      "end_time": 143328.0,
      "text": "shields microbes from external threats."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 143328.0,
      "end_time": 147926.0,
      "text": "Biofilms also enable interactions between individual cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 147926.0,
      "end_time": 151600.0,
      "text": "When microbes are packed against  each other in close proximity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 151600.0,
      "end_time": 152653.0,
      "text": "they can communicate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 152653.0,
      "end_time": 154521.0,
      "text": "exchange genetic information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 154521.0,
      "end_time": 158714.0,
      "text": "and engage in cooperative and competitive social behaviors."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 158714.0,
      "end_time": 160640.0,
      "text": "Take the soil in your garden,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 160640.0,
      "end_time": 163283.0,
      "text": "home to thousands of bacterial species."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 163283.0,
      "end_time": 165855.0,
      "text": "As one species colonizes a plant root,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 165855.0,
      "end_time": 170647.0,
      "text": "its individual cells might differentiate into various subpopulations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 170647.0,
      "end_time": 173350.0,
      "text": "each carrying out a specific task."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 173350.0,
      "end_time": 177445.0,
      "text": "Matrix producers pump out  the extracellular goo,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 177445.0,
      "end_time": 182082.0,
      "text": "swimmers assemble flagella and are free to move about or migrate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 182082.0,
      "end_time": 186708.0,
      "text": "and spore-formers produce dormant, tough endospores"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 186708.0,
      "end_time": 188187.0,
      "text": "that survive starvation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 188187.0,
      "end_time": 189607.0,
      "text": "temperature extremes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 189607.0,
      "end_time": 192057.0,
      "text": "and harmful radiation."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 192057.0,
      "end_time": 194380.0,
      "text": "This phenomenon is called  division of labor."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 194380.0,
      "end_time": 199300.0,
      "text": "Ultimately, it gives rise to  a sophisticated system of cooperation"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 199300.0,
      "end_time": 203932.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s somewhat like  a multicellular organism in itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 203932.0,
      "end_time": 208253.0,
      "text": "But because biofilms often contain many different microbes"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 208253.0,
      "end_time": 210365.0,
      "text": "that aren&#39;t closely related to each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 210365.0,
      "end_time": 213490.0,
      "text": "interactions can also be competitive."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 213490.0,
      "end_time": 216908.0,
      "text": "Bacteria launch vicious attacks  on their competitors"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 216908.0,
      "end_time": 219775.0,
      "text": "by secreting chemicals  into the environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 219775.0,
      "end_time": 225176.0,
      "text": "or by deploying molecular spears to inject nearby cells with toxins"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 225176.0,
      "end_time": 227981.0,
      "text": "that literally blow them up."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 227981.0,
      "end_time": 231201.0,
      "text": "In the end, competition  is all about resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 231201.0,
      "end_time": 233354.0,
      "text": "If one species eliminates another,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 233354.0,
      "end_time": 237120.0,
      "text": "it keeps more space and food for itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 237120.0,
      "end_time": 240850.0,
      "text": "Although this dramatic life cycle occurs beyond the limits of our vision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 240850.0,
      "end_time": 245743.0,
      "text": "microbial communities provide humans and other species with tangible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 245743.0,
      "end_time": 248646.0,
      "text": "and sometimes even delicious, benefits."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 248646.0,
      "end_time": 252442.0,
      "text": "Microbes make up a major fraction of the biomass on Earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 252442.0,
      "end_time": 255881.0,
      "text": "and play a critical role  within the global ecosystem"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 255881.0,
      "end_time": 258555.0,
      "text": "that supports all larger organisms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 258555.0,
      "end_time": 259945.0,
      "text": "including us."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 259945.0,
      "end_time": 262167.0,
      "text": "They produce much of the oxygen we breath,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 262167.0,
      "end_time": 266765.0,
      "text": "and are recruited to clean up environmental pollution, like oil spills,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 266765.0,
      "end_time": 268796.0,
      "text": "or to treat our waste water."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 268796.0,
      "end_time": 272814.0,
      "text": "Not to mention, biofilms are normal and flavor enhancing parts"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 272814.0,
      "end_time": 274945.0,
      "text": "of many of the foods we enjoy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 274945.0,
      "end_time": 276232.0,
      "text": "including cheese,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 276232.0,
      "end_time": 277286.0,
      "text": "salami,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 277286.0,
      "end_time": 279257.0,
      "text": "and kombucha."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 279257.0,
      "end_time": 281116.0,
      "text": "So the next time you brush your teeth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 281116.0,
      "end_time": 282798.0,
      "text": "bite into that cheese rind,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 282798.0,
      "end_time": 284442.0,
      "text": "sift through garden soil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 284442.0,
      "end_time": 286471.0,
      "text": "or skip a river stone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 286471.0,
      "end_time": 288269.0,
      "text": "look as close as you can."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 288269.0,
      "end_time": 291680.0,
      "text": "Imagine the microbial jungles  all around you"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 291680.0,
      "end_time": 301680.0,
      "text": "waiting to be discovered and explored."
    }
  ]
}